(44, 26, 17, 48, 2, 9, 9, 'from the Gentiles, unto whom now I send thee', 'Mission to the Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the shared mission to the Gentiles in both passages. Acts 26:17 speaks of being sent to the Gentiles, while Galatians 2:9 mentions going unto the heathen, indicating a common focus on outreach to non-Jewish people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
