(44, 26, 18, 44, 20, 32, 32, 'inheritance among them which are sanctified', 'Inheritance Among the Sanctified', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of inheritance among those who are sanctified. Acts 26:18 speaks of receiving an inheritance through faith, while Acts 20:32 mentions giving an inheritance among the sanctified.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 18, 49, 5, 8, 8, 'from darkness to light', 'Transition from Darkness to Light', 'Both passages emphasize the transformation from darkness to light, highlighting the change in spiritual state. Acts 26:18 speaks of turning from darkness to light, while Ephesians 5:8 states that believers are now light in the Lord.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 18, 23, 42, 7, 7, 'to open their eyes', 'Opening Eyes and Deliverance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of opening blind eyes and bringing people out of darkness. Acts 26:18 speaks of turning individuals from darkness to light, while Isaiah 42:7 mentions opening the blind eyes and bringing those in darkness out of prison.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 18, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'darkness to light', 'Light and Darkness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from darkness to light, highlighting the transformative power of God. Acts 26:18 speaks of turning from darkness to light, while 2 Corinthians 4:6 describes God shining light in our hearts.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 18, 51, 1, 12, 14, 'from darkness to light', 'Inheritance and Deliverance from Darkness', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from darkness to light and the reception of forgiveness of sins. They highlight the theme of being delivered from the power of darkness and receiving an inheritance among the sanctified.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 19, 23, 50, 5, 5, 'not disobedient', 'Obedience to Divine Calling', 'Both passages emphasize a commitment to divine instruction. Acts 26:19 speaks of not being ''disobedient'' to a vision, while Isaiah 50:5 mentions being ''not rebellious'' to God''s call.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
