(44, 26, 19, 48, 1, 16, 16, 'not disobedient unto the heavenly vision', 'Divine Revelation and Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation and the immediate response to it. In both passages, the emphasis is on receiving a heavenly vision or revelation and acting upon it without delay.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 19, 24, 20, 9, 9, 'not disobedient unto the heavenly vision', 'Divine Calling and Inner Urgency', 'Both passages emphasize a strong compulsion to speak God''s message. In Acts, Paul expresses obedience to a heavenly vision, while Jeremiah describes a burning fire within him that compels him to speak despite his reluctance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 19, 2, 4, 13, 14, 'not disobedient unto the heavenly vision', 'Obedience to Divine Calling', 'This connection highlights the theme of responding to divine direction. Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to God''s call, with Paul affirming his compliance and Moses expressing reluctance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
