(44, 26, 19, 32, 1, 3, 3, 'not disobedient unto the heavenly vision', 'Disobedience to Divine Command', 'This connection highlights the theme of disobedience to God''s call. In Acts, Paul asserts his obedience to a heavenly vision, while Jonah explicitly chooses to flee from the presence of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 20, 40, 3, 8, 8, 'works meet for repentance', 'Fruits of Repentance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of demonstrating repentance through actions. Acts 26:20 speaks of ''works meet for repentance,'' while Matthew 3:8 calls for ''fruits meet for repentance.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 20, 44, 3, 19, 19, 'repent and turn to God', 'Call to Repentance and Conversion', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of repentance. Acts 26:20 mentions the call to ''repent and turn to God,'' while Acts 3:19 urges to ''repent... and be converted.'' This connection highlights the consistent biblical theme of repentance leading to forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 20, 44, 2, 38, 38, 'repent and turn to God', 'Call to Repentance and Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance in both passages. Acts 26:20 emphasizes the need to ''repent and turn to God,'' while Acts 2:38 calls for repentance and baptism for the remission of sins.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 20, 55, 2, 25, 26, 'repent and turn to God', 'Connection of Repentance Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance in both passages. Acts 26:20 emphasizes the call to ''repent and turn to God,'' while 2 Timothy 2:25 speaks of God granting ''repentance to the acknowledging of the truth.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 20, 40, 9, 13, 13, 'repent and turn to God', 'Call to Repentance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of repentance, highlighting the call for sinners to turn to God. Acts 26:20 speaks of doing ''works meet for repentance,'' while Matthew 9:13 focuses on calling ''sinners to repentance.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 20, 42, 19, 8, 9, 'repent and turn to God', 'Repentance and Salvation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of repentance leading to salvation. In Acts, the call to ''repent and turn to God'' aligns with Zaccheus''s actions of restitution and giving, demonstrating true repentance.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 20, 61, 1, 5, 8, 'repent and turn to God', 'Connection of Repentance and Virtue', 'This connection highlights the call to ''repent and turn to God'' in Acts, which parallels the emphasis on adding virtues in 2 Peter. Both passages stress the importance of active faith and moral development as essential components of a believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 21, 44, 21, 30, 31, 'went about to kill me', 'Paul''s Persecution in Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the violent intent of the Jews towards Paul, highlighting the danger he faced in the temple. Acts 26:21 refers to the Jews wanting to kill him, which is mirrored in Acts 21:30-31 where they actively attempt to do so.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 21, 44, 21, 27, 27, 'in the temple', 'Paul''s Temple Encounter', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s experience in the temple, where he faced hostility from the Jews. Acts 21:27 describes the Jews stirring up the people against him, leading to the situation Paul references in Acts 26:21.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 21, 44, 22, 22, 22, 'the Jews caught me in the temple', 'Response to Paul''s Accusation', 'Both passages emphasize the Jews'' hostility towards Paul. In Acts 26:21, Paul states he was caught in the temple, while Acts 22:22 shows the crowd''s violent reaction, declaring he should not live.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 21, 44, 23, 12, 15, 'went about to kill me', 'Conspiracy Against Paul', 'Both passages emphasize the plot against Paul, with Acts 26:21 referencing the Jews'' intent to kill him, while Acts 23:12-15 details their conspiracy to do so. This connection highlights the ongoing threat to Paul''s life from the Jewish leaders.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 26, 21, 44, 25, 3, 3, 'went about to kill me', 'Plot Against Paul', 'Both passages emphasize the Jews'' intent to kill Paul. Acts 25:3 describes their plot to kill him, while Acts 26:21 recounts their actions in the temple leading to his capture.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
